- n Subscript[k, j] or n Subscript[k, j] on the Wick state ws depending on \
the occupation sj = 0 or sj = 1, respectively, of the bare fermion mode kj. \
WickProject[ws, mat -> {s1, s2, ..., sm}] applies the projection for the \
dressed fermion modes described by m*n row-orthogonal isometric matrix (mat . \
mat^\\[Dagger] = I), where n is the total number of bare modes.", 
